{"author":{"id":"51b4135134c5b2ca49c9c04b6a67bb5314f924f2c46be29f32135fb5f94fdc38"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1708648953,"nonce":"8RTOCSsYT0Zn3bUUOfrjUTuHGb0=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOCGKeh86AKTKU","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/1141","origin":"github"},"title":"Add ability to add a label when creating a new bug","message":"It would be really useful to have the option to add labels directly when creating a bug, particularly when I'm importing a bunch of tasks or projects manually from a todo list.\n\nAlso, when I'm in the middle of something and notice an issue that needs fixing but I'm not able to address it immediately, remembering to go back and add a label can be a bit disruptive to my workflow.\n\nAdding a `--label` switch to the add command, and maybe a `#Label:` prefix in the file format for the -F switch would be helpful.","files":null}]}